  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activity 05: Great Lakes Focal Points Meeting</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Great Lakes Region Focal Points Meeting involving National Committee (NC) members from both Anglophone and Francophone countries in the region was conducted through a series of activities that included: (I) A total of 6 zoom meetings focusing on IBV crosscutting themes; (ii) Research and production of 7 country-specific case studies; and (iii) Generation of regional strategies and recommendations (Francophone and Anglophone states) to facilitate collaboration among states, regional, and continental inter-governmental organizations. As part of adopting to the current programming challenges raised by COVID-19, the above events involved 29 Focal Persons selected from active members of the respective NC&#x2019;s represented their respective countries.</narrative>
  </description>
